I need some one with privileges (@jenlampton @Geoff St. Pierre (serundeputy) @Mike McCaffrey ???) to delete the repo https://github.com/backdrop-contrib/editablefields I created in a bad moment. I'm porting this module and forgot to import it from drupal git. I have it ready to transfer to backdrop-contrib in my repo https://github.com/robertgarrigos/editablefields but cannot do so untill the former is deleted. Thanks and sorry.

backdrop-contrib/editablefields
Allows you to make some fields editable from the display. - backdrop-contrib/editablefields
robertgarrigos/editablefields
This module allows fields to be edited on a node's display - robertgarrigos/editablefields

Hi, Robert Garrigos. Welcome to the Backdrop CMS community on Zulip. I'm your friendly neighborhood Dragonbot. Try '@Dragonbot help' for a list of things I can help you with. There are lots of friendly humans that hang around here, so please feel free to ask questions.

Here is a short (3 min) video to help you navigate Zulip. https://youtu.be/DN8YL2MrsSU
@Robert Garrigos I don't have access to delete ... @klonos?

@Robert Garrigos but you dont need to transfer the repo. Just add the contrib repo as a remote on your local and push your code to that. I've coded probably a hundred contribs and never transferred, always pushed from local straight to contrib.
right. thanks @docwilmot . will do that

Done: https://github.com/backdrop-contrib/editablefields
